          Using complex real-world structured, text, and image data Memorial Sloan Kettering (MSK) has collected over the past 20+ years, the
           Research Data Scientist
          will work closely with software engineers and applied data scientists to develop and implement advanced machine learning methods to power MSK’s efforts to build a world-class analytics platform for healthcare data, patient outcomes, and cancer treatments.
          The right candidate will have a track record of developing new machine learning methods and applying them to complex problems. To that end, the Research Data Scientist will actively contribute to the research community through collaborations with academic partners, publishing in peer-reviewed journals and attending top-tier machine learning conferences while working with internal teams to further the use of machine learning at MSK.
